## 3 Method

In this section, we outline the proposed multi-agent translation framework (i.e., CRAT) that leverages the Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) mechanism and causality-enhanced self-reflection. The framework addresses the challenge of translating uncertain terms with accuracy and contextual relevance, overcoming limitations observed in LLMs when encountering such terms. The overall pipeline is presented in Figure [2](https://arxiv.org/html/2410.21067v1#S3.F2 "Figure 2 â€£ 3.1 Task Formulation â€£ 3 Method â€£ CRAT: A Multi-Agent Framework for Causality-Enhanced Reflective and Retrieval-Augmented Translation with Large Language Models").

### 3.1 Task Formulation

